      <div><div class="container no-gutters row bs-1col paragraph paragraph--type-bp-simple paragraph--view-mode-default">
  
  <div class="col-sm-12 bs-region bs-region--main">
    
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-bp-text field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><h3>Howard D. Johnson Award</h3>

<h5>2023 Recipient:</h5>

<h4>Genna Miller, Lecturing Fellow of Economics</h4>

<div data-embed-button="embed_image" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.square_smaller" data-entity-embed-display-settings="[]" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="459ad664-d1aa-4956-bbd0-f6905a968e0b" data-langcode="en" class="align-right embedded-entity"><div>
  
  
            <div class="field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item">  <img src="/sites/trinity.duke.edu/files/styles/square_smaller/public/images/2023_Genna_Miller_Portrait_Teaching_Award-1.jpg?h=cb5829b5&amp;itok=NRA2W5DC" width="225" height="225" alt="Genna Miller" loading="lazy" class="image-style-square-smaller">


</div>
      
</div>
</div>


<p><span><span><strong><span><span>From students: </span></span></strong><span><span>âProf. Millerâs class was full of discussion and incorporated many different types of learning to accommodate all types of learners. The different activities we did in class were very helpful and ensured that we were reaching higher levels of Bloomâs Taxonomy [of learning], and not just memorizing information.â</span></span></span></span></p>

